title: For Sale:  Built AR-15 Pistol, 10.5" 5.56 Shockwave Blade Brace and SST1 cheek saddle Palmetto State lower
postcontent:
I'm selling my built AR-15 pistol. This is not an SBR.
It has a 10.5" barrel and is chambered in 5.56 with a 1/7 twist. I've put around 500 rounds through it without any malfunctions whatsoever. The muzzle device is a clone of the Noveske KX3 meant to redirect blast forward and away from the shooter. This 10.5" pistol has less concussion than a 16" with a compensator and is very comfortable to shoot. The gas system is carbine length, and the barrel is industry standard 4150 melonited chrome moly vanadium. The quadrail has an endcap installed, and I've also got an A2 birdcage flash hider if you want to make the package as short as possible. The irons sights are Magpul MBUS and they were zeroed by my Army friend. The red dot is not included. The side rail covers are authentic Knight's Armament panel covers. The top rail cover is a standard ergo rubber ladder cover. The bolt carrier group and the lower receiver are both mil-spec Palmetto State Armory, and I colorfilled the lower with high temp enamel. The lower parts kit and trigger are Mil-Spec PSA as well. The charging handle has been upgraded with an extended latch. The buffer tube assembly is the steel setup from KAK specifically designed for the Shockwave Blade arm brace. Mounted to the Shockwave Blade is the Command Arms SST1 cheek saddle. It is securely mounted and allows you the rest your cheek comfortably. The front QD socket mount is from Magpul, and the endplate QD mount is from Impact Weapons Components up in Loveland. It is ready to run a sling with QD attachments either as single or dual point. The sling isn't included. The Shockwave Blade and SST1 cheek saddle setup works very well and far outperforms the Sigbrace. I will include paper copies of the 3 relevant ATF letters regarding the Shockwave Blade, the SST1 cheek saddle, and AR pistol usage. 
This is a fantastic truck gun, home defense gun, or just fun range toy. It shoots very well and I'm sad to see it go. The build is one of a kind.

postcontent: 0% Shoot First Pay Later Financing Available On Everything In Our Online Gun Store! Click Here To View This Suppressor On Our Website Shoot First Pay Later Details & Application Click Here SILENCER CO. 22 SPARROW •Patented Multi-Part Containment (MPC) technology assesses the molten lead & carbon debris build-up issue associated w/the absense of copper jackets on .22 LR cartridges by allowing the user to easily disassemble the silencer for routine cleaning & maintenance after heavy use   •Alloy steel & heat-treated 17-4 PH SS construction   •Chemical & solvent resistant stainless steel   •Steel thread (1/2"x28TPI) mount   •O-ring engagement keeps barrel threads clean & silencer securely mounted   •Serialized outer tube is protected   •Compatible Calibers: .22 LR, .17 HMR, .22 Mag., .22 WMR, & 5.7x28 FN   •Full Auto Rated on .22 LR   •Sound Reduction: 41dB   •Black Oxide finish   •Lifetime Warranty   •Size (Diameter x Length): 1.062" x 5.08" &nbs  Buying & Registering A suppressor/silencer This page will guide you through the process for legally buying a Suppressor / Silencer Buying a suppressor is much easier than you may think. Just follow the steps below or give us a call and we will be happy to walk you through the entire process. What paperwork will I need to legally register a suppressor? There are two main methods for registering your suppressor:   Registration using a “Trust” (easiest method)   Registration in your name   Option 1 Registration using a “Trust”   Set up your trust   Purchase your suppressor online at grabagun.com   Fill out your Form 4 and Mail in your $200 payment to ATF   Sit back and relax because you are done!   It will cost approximately $100 more to buy using the trust method, but it will save a ton of time and provide a great deal more flexibility than an individually registered suppressor. There are many advantages to using a trust for registering a suppressor.  Some of these advantages include:   more than one person (family or friends) can legally use the suppressor if they are listed on the trust   one trust can be used for multiple suppressors   trusts can be modified to add or remove people without approval from the ATF   most importantly you DO NOT have to get fingerprint cards or your county's Chief Law Enforcement Officer to sign off on the purchase.  These benefits will save a lot of time and hassle down the road.   There are many places you can go online or locally to download a Trust to be used for registering your suppressor. Here are a few examples which range in price from $99 - $129:   http://199trust.com/   http://www.thefirearmlawyers.com/   http://www.guntrust.com/   Option 2 Registration to an individual   Purchase your suppressor online at grabagun.com   Fill out Form 4 and $200 payment for ATF   Obtain 2 Passport Photos   Obtain Chief Law Enforcement Officer Sign Off (Must be in the county you are a resident in)   Two copies of fingerprint cards (FBI form FD-258)   Complete Certificate of Compliance – ATF Form 5330.20   This is a less expensive method for registering your suppressor since you will not have to pay the $100 for a trust to be set up. However, you will be the sole owner of the suppressor and will have to be present any time the suppressor is being used (this includes your spouse and kids). In addition you will have to complete several additional steps (Steps 3 – 6 above) that you do not have to complete if you opt to register your suppressor using a trust. FAQ’s Am I eligible to own a suppressor? If you are 21 years old or older AND able to legally possess a firearm then you should be eligible to purchase a suppressor. This also assumes you have verified it is legal to own in your State and County. Is it legal to own a suppressor in my State? Suppressor ownership and hunting with a suppressor is legal in most States. Please reference the map, provided by the American Suppressor Association, below to see if suppressors are legal in your State. This map is for reference and you should be sure to check your State and County laws before making any suppressor purchase.    * Minnesota hunting law to take effect August 1, 2015.* Maine Hunting and Shall Sign laws to take effect mid October.   How long is the wait? Wait times will vary throughout the year but can be anywhere from 3-6 months. Once you submit your paperwork you will be able to contact the ATF to inquire about the status of your paperwork. Just keep in mind this is a government process that is out of all of our control and you will need to be patient. As they have told us in the past, “It will be ready when it is ready”. 7 Step Process To Order A Suppressor From Gun Pro:   Use the Gun Pro FFL Locator for Class III dealers to find a dealer in your area. If you can't find a Class III dealer contact us and we will assist you in locating one.   Make sure the dealer will take “Title II” or suppressor transfers and inquire about their transfer fee. (Fees average $75-$100)   Purchase your suppressor on WWW.GunProDeals.Com and choose that dealer from the drop down menu at checkout   If the dealer you want is not currently in our database please have your dealer email us a copy of their FFL and SOT to REDACTED We will update your order and let you know once we have the information.   Once our transfer forms are in place with your dealer, usually 2 weeks, we will email you the Form 4 information you will need to complete. You can complete this information and submit it right away. Please check with your local transfer dealer for their policy and procedures.   We will transfer the suppressor to your local dealer and they will contact you once your Form 4 has been approved.   At any time in the process if you are not sure about a step, or are needing help please contact us at REDACTED   We are unable to process cancellations, returns or refunds for silencers or any NFA items once the order is placed.

There are two main methods for registering your suppressor:   Registration using a “Trust” (easiest method)   Registration in your name   Option 1 Registration using a “Trust”   Set up your trust   Purchase your suppressor online at grabagun.com   Fill out your Form 4 and Mail in your $200 payment to ATF   Sit back and relax because you are done!   It will cost approximately $100 more to buy using the trust method, but it will save a ton of time and provide a great deal more flexibility than an individually registered suppressor. There are many advantages to using a trust for registering a suppressor.  Some of these advantages include:   more than one person (family or friends) can legally use the suppressor if they are listed on the trust   one trust can be used for multiple suppressors   trusts can be modified to add or remove people without approval from the ATF   most importantly you DO NOT have to get fingerprint cards or your county's Chief Law Enforcement Officer to sign off on the purchase.  These benefits will save a lot of time and hassle down the road. However, you will be the sole owner of the suppressor and will have to be present any time the suppressor is being used (this includes your spouse and kids). In addition you will have to complete several additional steps (Steps 3 – 6 above) that you do not have to complete if you opt to register your suppressor using a trust. postcontent: Click Here To View This SBR On Our Website Shoot Now Pay Later Financing Details & Application Click Here Spike's Cmprsr 5.56mm 8.1" 30rd Frgd Spike's Tactical ST Compressor, Semi-automatic Rifle, 5.56MM, 8.1 Barrel, Black Finish, Magpul AFG2 Angled Fore Grip, 30Rd, Forged, No Suppressor STR5110-NOS Buying & Registering A suppressor/silencer This page will guide you through the process for legally buying a Suppressor / Silencer Buying a suppressor is much easier than you may think. Just follow the steps below or give us a call and we will be happy to walk you through the entire process. What paperwork will I need to legally register a suppressor? There are two main methods for registering your suppressor:   Registration using a “Trust” (easiest method)   Registration in your name   Option 1 Registration using a “Trust”   Set up your trust   Purchase your suppressor online at grabagun.com   Fill out your Form 4 and Mail in your $200 payment to ATF   Sit back and relax because you are done!   It will cost approximately $100 more to buy using the trust method, but it will save a ton of time and provide a great deal more flexibility than an individually registered suppressor. There are many advantages to using a trust for registering a suppressor.  Some of these advantages include:   more than one person (family or friends) can legally use the suppressor if they are listed on the trust   one trust can be used for multiple suppressors   trusts can be modified to add or remove people without approval from the ATF   most importantly you DO NOT have to get fingerprint cards or your county's Chief Law Enforcement Officer to sign off on the purchase.  These benefits will save a lot of time and hassle down the road.   There are many places you can go online or locally to download a Trust to be used for registering your suppressor. Here are a few examples which range in price from $99 - $129:   http://199trust.com/   http://www.thefirearmlawyers.com/   http://www.guntrust.com/   Option 2 Registration to an individual   Purchase your suppressor online at grabagun.com   Fill out Form 4 and $200 payment for ATF   Obtain 2 Passport Photos   Obtain Chief Law Enforcement Officer Sign Off (Must be in the county you are a resident in)   Two copies of fingerprint cards (FBI form FD-258)   Complete Certificate of Compliance – ATF Form 5330.20   This is a less expensive method for registering your suppressor since you will not have to pay the $100 for a trust to be set up. However, you will be the sole owner of the suppressor and will have to be present any time the suppressor is being used (this includes your spouse and kids). In addition you will have to complete several additional steps (Steps 3 – 6 above) that you do not have to complete if you opt to register your suppressor using a trust. FAQ’s Am I eligible to own a suppressor? If you are 21 years old or older AND able to legally possess a firearm then you should be eligible to purchase a suppressor. This also assumes you have verified it is legal to own in your State and County. Is it legal to own a suppressor in my State? Suppressor ownership and hunting with a suppressor is legal in most States. Please reference the map, provided by the American Suppressor Association, below to see if suppressors are legal in your State. This map is for reference and you should be sure to check your State and County laws before making any suppressor purchase.    * Minnesota hunting law to take effect August 1, 2015.* Maine Hunting and Shall Sign laws to take effect mid October.   How long is the wait? Wait times will vary throughout the year but can be anywhere from 3-6 months. Once you submit your paperwork you will be able to contact the ATF to inquire about the status of your paperwork. Just keep in mind this is a government process that is out of all of our control and you will need to be patient. As they have told us in the past, “It will be ready when it is ready”. 7 Step Process To Order A Suppressor From Gun Pro:   Use the Gun Pro FFL Locator for Class III dealers to find a dealer in your area. If you can't find a Class III dealer contact us and we will assist you in locating one.   Make sure the dealer will take “Title II” or suppressor transfers and inquire about their transfer fee. (Fees average $75-$100)   Purchase your suppressor on WWW.GunProDeals.Com and choose that dealer from the drop down menu at checkout   If the dealer you want is not currently in our database please have your dealer email us a copy of their FFL and SOT to REDACTED We will update your order and let you know once we have the information.   Once our transfer forms are in place with your dealer, usually 2 weeks, we will email you the Form 4 information you will need to complete. You can complete this information and submit it right away. Please check with your local transfer dealer for their policy and procedures.   We will transfer the suppressor to your local dealer and they will contact you once your Form 4 has been approved.   At any time in the process if you are not sure about a step, or are needing help please contact us at REDACTED   We are unable to process cancellations, returns or refunds for silencers or any NFA items once the order is placed.
